This kofun is one of the prominent Kofuns within the Yame Kofun Group, ranking third in size after {{ill|Iwatoyama Kofun|ja|岩戸山古墳|12=draft|12=draft}} and {{ill|Sekijinzan Kofun|ja|石人山古墳|12=draft|12=draft}}. The mound faces west and features a two-tiered construction adorned with {{ill|fukiishi|ja|葺き石|12=draft|12=draft}} (paving stones) and {{ill|haniwa|ja|埴輪|12=draft|12=draft}}.<ref>「Nihon Kofun Daijiten」p.318</ref>

Based on surface-collected cylindrical haniwa fragments, the construction of Zenzōzuka Kofun is estimated to date from the early to mid-6th century.<ref>[http://www.town.hirokawa.fukuoka.jp/konnamachi/accessmap/popupbunkazai/popbunka_9.htm Zenzōzuka Kofun, Hirokawa Town]</ref> It is considered contemporaneous with the {{ill|Tsurumiyama Kofun|ja|鶴見山古墳|12=draft|12=draft}} and slightly postdates the {{ill|Nobaba Kofun|ja|乗場古墳|12=draft|12=draft}}.<ref>"Exhibition Catalog of the Iwatoyama Historical Museum," p.9.</ref>

