{{Infobox ancient site|type = [[Zenpokoenfun]]| name=Zenzōzuka Kofun| image=[[File:Zenzozuka kofun in Hirokawa.jpg|250px]] |part_of={{ill|Yame Kofun Group|ja|八女古墳群|qq=draft|qq=draft}}| location={{ill|Hirokawa, Fukuoka|ja|広川町 (福岡県)|qq=draft|qq=draft}}, {{ill|Yame District, Fukuoka|ja|八女郡|qq=draft|qq=draft}}, Fukuoka Prefecture| coordinates={{coordinates|33|14|02.4|N|130|34|04.2|E|}}| Shape=Keyhole-shaped tumulus (前方後円墳)| area=Total length: 95 meters| built=Early to mid-6th century| Excavated Artifacts=Haniwa| Historic Site Designation=Designated as a National Historic Site in {{ill|1978|ja|1978th year|qq=draft|qq=draft}}| }}
'''Zenzōzuka Kofun''' (善蔵塚古墳) is a {{ill|keyhole-shaped tumulus|ja|前方後円墳|1=Zenpokoenfun|1=Zenpokoenfun|qq=draft|qq=draft}} located in {{ill|Hirokawa, Fukuoka|ja|広川町 (福岡県)|qq=draft|qq=draft}}, {{ill|Yame District, Fukuoka|ja|八女郡|qq=draft|qq=draft}}, Japan. It is Historic Site1 as a National Historic Site and is part of the {{ill|Yame Kofun Group|ja|八女古墳群|qq=draft|qq=draft}}.
This kofun is one of the prominent Kofuns within the Yame Kofun Group, Ranking third in size after {{ill|Iwatoyama Kofun|ja|岩戸山古墳|1=Iwato-yama Kofun|qq=draft|qq=draft}} and {{ill|Sekijinzan Kofun|ja|石人山古墳|qq=draft|qq=draft}}. The mound faces west and features a two-tiered construction adorned with {{ill|fukiishi|ja|葺き石|qq=draft|qq=draft}} (paving stones) and {{ill|haniwa|ja|埴輪|qq=draft|qq=draft}}.<ref>「Nihon Kofun Daijiten」p.318</ref>
Based on surface-collected cylindrical haniwa fragments, the construction of Zenzōzuka Kofun is estimated to date from the early to mid-6th century.<ref>[http://www.town.hirokawa.fukuoka.jp/konnamachi/accessmap/popupbunkazai/popbunka_9.htm Zenzōzuka Kofun, Hirokawa Town]</ref> It is considered contemporaneous with the {{ill|Tsurumiyama Kofun|ja|鶴見山古墳|qq=draft|qq=draft}} and slightly postdates the {{ill|Nobaba Kofun|ja|乗場古墳|qq=draft|qq=draft}}.<ref>"Exhibition Catalog of the Iwatoyama Historical Museum," p.9.</ref>
