Based on surface-collected cylindrical haniwa fragments, the construction of Zenzōzuka Kofun is estimated to date from the early to mid-6th century.<ref>[http://www.town.hirokawa.fukuoka.jp/konnamachi/accessmap/popupbunkazai/popbunka_9.htm Zenzōzuka Kofun, Hirokawa Town]</ref> It is considered contemporaneous with the {{ill|Tsurumiyama Kofun|ja|鶴見山古墳|qq=draft|qq=draft}} and slightly postdates the {{ill|Nobaba Kofun|ja|乗場古墳|qq=draft|qq=draft}}.<ref>"Exhibition Catalog of the Iwatoyama Historical Museum," p.9.</ref>
